{"cursor":"25991","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"In category theory, a branch of mathematics, the abstract notion of a 'limit'\ncaptures the essential properties of universal constructions such as products,\npullbacks and inverse limits. The dual notion of a 'colimit' generalizes\nconstructions such as disjoint unions, direct sums, coproducts, pushouts and\ndirect limits.\n\nLimits and colimits, like the strongly related notions of universal properties\nand adjoint functors, exist at a high level of abstraction. In order to\nunderstand them, it is helpful to first study the specific examples these\nconcepts are meant to generalize.\n","linknr":252,"url":"Limit_(category_theory)","recorded":1362585234,"links":23,"instances":["category_theory","mathematics","category_theory","category_theory","category_theory","category_theory"],"pdf":["http://katmat.math.uni-bremen.de/acc/acc.pdf","http://katmat.math.uni-bremen.de/acc/acc.pdf"],"categories":["Limits (category theory)|"],"headings":["Definition","Examples","Properties","Functors and limits","A note on terminology","References","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/81/Functor_cone_%28extended%29.svg/196px-Functor_cone_%28extended%29.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/7/f/2/7f20aa0b3691b496aec21cf356f63e04.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/7/f/2/7f20aa0b3691b496aec21cf356f63e04.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5a/Functor_co-cone_%28extended%29.svg/196px-Functor_co-cone_%28extended%29.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/f/f6/CategoricalPullback-01.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/a/a/a/aaa0e2a9d8ebbf0f3cdbc03e22996edf.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/c/e/3/ce3d14d10192b310704626eb6ebcf1be.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/4/c/9/4c9ebaf91efa27d379a0bb92a8b97f46.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/9/d/a/9dabf7de6c500cbd897e06007d5cd3a4.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/5/0/1/501bc0463052dfe7b63032cf1799e787.png","//upload.wik